data.name: Allen Frye Jr.
history: I think Guilherme is a very solid opponent. Heâ€™s a long, quick striker who can move very well.Â
I try to train for every fight as if Iâ€™m fighting for the world title so I would say the only difference is the opponent Iâ€™m preparing for.

I started back in late 2020 early 2021. I was trying to play professional basketball and it didnâ€™t work out, so I wanted to pick up another hobby and found MMA. I had no intentions of fighting until after a few months of training, then I wanted to test myself.
Ultimate Battlegrounds Heavyweight ChampionÂ
Blue belt in JiujitsuÂ
My toughest fight to date was my last fight with Justin Frazier because I tore some cartilage in my rib in the first 20 seconds, so that was some adversity to fight through.
My favorite fighter is Israel Adesanya because he never turns down a tough fight and his patience on the feet is something to look up to.
I went to North Carolina Wesleyan University and studied Organizational Administration with a concentration in sports.
I am a bartender, bouncer, and a basketball coach.

Iâ€™m originally from New York.I have a dog, 3 sisters, my mom and my stepdad, they mean the world to me. My real dad passed away when i was 3 years old and my lifelong dream is to make him as proud as I can.Â
I would love to meet LeBron James, Tom Brady, and Georges St. Pierre
I love to hangout with friends and family, playing music, and playing basketball when Iâ€™m not training for a fight.Â
